{"_id":"1P1O0BHojSINAbRg","name":"Deadly Aim (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your can strike your enemies’ weak points and deal more damage.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Base attack bonus +1.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: When you take the attack or full attack action with weapons (including a solarian’s solar manifestation, but not spells or other special abilities of any kind), you can take a –2 penalty to your attack rolls. If you do, those attacks deal additional damage equal to half your base attack bonus (minimum 1).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"name":"Diehard","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You are especially hard to kill. Your wounds quickly stabilize when you’re grievously wounded.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Benefit</strong>: When you are dying, you can spend the required Resolve Points to stabilize and 1 Resolve Point to stay in the fight (regaining 1 Hit Point) in the same round.</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Normal</strong>: You must use Resolve Points to stabilize and to stay in the fight in separate rounds.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"4WOgAfmOTll6oqGo"}
{"name":"Diligent Searcher","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your ordered mind allows you to thoroughly search an area in less time.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Perception 1 rank.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain a +1 insight bonus to Perception checks. In addition, you can take 20 on a Perception check to search in only 5 times the usual amount of time, meaning it takes only 5 minutes for you to exhaustively search an area no more than 20 feet by 20 feet.<br></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Normal</strong>: It takes 20 minutes to exhaustively search an area no more than 20 feet by 20 feet.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"The Chimera Mystery","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"6olLiUvLYSMvnKcI"}
{"_id":"1P1O0BHojSINAbRg","name":"Deadly Aim (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your can strike your enemies’ weak points and deal more damage.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Base attack bonus +1.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: When you take the attack or full attack action with weapons (including a solarian’s solar manifestation, but not spells or other special abilities of any kind), you can take a –2 penalty to your attack rolls. If you do, those attacks deal additional damage equal to half your base attack bonus (minimum 1).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"name":"Far Shot (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You remain accurate at longer ranges.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Base attack bonus +1.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You take only a –1 penalty per full range increment between you and your target when using a ranged weapon.<br><br><strong>Normal</strong>: You take a –2 penalty per full range increment between you and your target.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"i3l4HZjn6MBEWiVe"}
{"name":"Fast Talk","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can baffle a foe with chatter to disguise the start of battle.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Bluff 5 ranks.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You can distract a creature with a confusing barrage of words, causing it to be surprised at the beginning of combat. You can use this ability only on a creature you are able to converse with (it must be able to see or hear you and understand your words) prior to the beginning of combat, and you must continue to converse with it until combat begins. You can’t use this ability if you are the one to instigate combat or if you are unaware at the start of combat.<br></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\">When the GM declares that combat has begun, but before initiative is rolled, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to attempt a Bluff check against a single creature that this ability can affect. The DC is equal to 15 + the target’s total Perception skill bonus, or 20 + 1-1/2 × the target’s CR, whichever is higher. If your check is successful, the target creature is considered unaware at the start of combat, allowing other creatures (including yourself) to act in a surprise round. Once you have attempted to use this ability on a creature, whether or not you succeed, it is immune to this ability for 24 hours.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"i5giuY838Czbb6Qa"}
{"name":"Four-Handed Hacker","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>When you hack a computer, it’s a two-front war.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Computers 1 rank, four or more hands.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: When you use the hack system task of Computers, if you have two hacking kits, your hacking attempt takes half the time (minimum 1 full action). You can also add, destroy, disable, remove, or repair a system or module in half the usual time.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"VtY7yDuCmw0LQyMS"}
{"name":"Frightening Injection","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You accompany your injections with a promise of terrible effects that shakes your target’s resolve.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Intimidate 3 ranks.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: When you successfully inject a creature with a substance (including a biohacker’s biohack) using a weapon that has the injection special property, you can attempt an Intimidate check to demoralize that creature as a move action before the end of your turn. A creature can be affected by this ability only once per day.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Character Operation Manual","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"DVR7J2rdXxfdosvi"}
{"name":"Great Cleave (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can strike many adjacent foes with a single blow.<br /><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Str 13, Cleave, base attack bonus +4.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: If you strike a second target with the Cleave feat, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to make a melee attack against each subsequent foe that is both adjacent to the last target and within your reach, as long as you hit the previous foe. You can&rsquo;t attack an individual foe more than once during this attack action.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"bMjPH2VpKBHxpdRJ"}
{"name":"Heavy Armor Proficiency (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You know how to use heavy armor.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Str 13, proficiency in light armor.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain proficiency in heavy armor (see page 242).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"zxBtaClmQw38z7LS"}
{"name":"Heavy Weapon Proficiency (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You know how to use heavy weapons.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Str 13, proficiency in small arms and longarms.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain proficiency in heavy weapons (see page 243).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"Ssw8itpOPE45uFzO"}
{"name":"Improved Combat Maneuver (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You are particularly skilled with a specific combat maneuver.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Base attack bonus +1.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: Choose one combat maneuver (bull rush, dirty trick, disarm, grapple, reposition, sunder, or trip). You gain a +4 bonus to your attack roll to resolve that combat maneuver.<br></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Special</strong>: You can take Improved Combat Maneuver multiple times. The effects don’t stack. Each time you take the feat, it applies to a new combat maneuver.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"0Pq35gvSI2JlD682"}
{"name":"Improved Critical (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Attacks with your chosen weapon are harder to shake off.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Base attack bonus +8.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: When you score a critical hit with a weapon, increase the DC to resist that weapon’s critical effect by 2.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"8BuU1VMQgMbMsz0i"}
{"name":"Improved Initiative (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your quick reflexes allow you to react rapidly to danger.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain a +4 bonus to initiative checks.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"0H0bEoQ96KX05ke2"}
{"name":"Improved Iron Will","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your clarity of thought allows you to resist mental attacks.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Iron Will, character level 5th.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You can spend 1 RP to reroll a failed Will save (see page 243).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"wkYOPC6hK4otQ4K8"}
{"name":"Iron Will","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You are more resistant to mental effects.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain a +2 bonus to Will saving throws.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"d7o4eg6e0xgstNfQ"}
{"name":"Light Armor Proficiency (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You know how to use light armor.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain proficiency in light armor (see Armor Proficiency on page 242).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"RbAOd8DeGs8NB54x"}
{"name":"Lightning Reflexes","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You have faster reflexes than normal.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain a +2 bonus to Reflex saving throws.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"bTzOH89OmNana18M"}
{"name":"Longarm Proficiency (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You know how to use longarms.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Proficiency in small arms.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain proficiency in longarms (see Weapon Proficiency on page 243).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"L7RuZ5Mvv7knW70t"}
{"name":"Medical Expert","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You are an expert at medical science and caring for the ill.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Life Science 1 rank, Medicine 1 rank, Physical Science 1 rank.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You can use the Medicine skill in conjunction with a medpatch or sprayflesh to treat deadly wounds as a full action. If you have an ability that enables you to treat deadly wounds more often but with a longer time frame (such as the envoy’s surgeon expertise talent), you cannot use this feat to use that ability more quickly. When used in this way, the medpatch or sprayflesh does not perform any of its normal functions. You can also use the Medicine skill to provide longterm care with just a medkit.<br></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Normal</strong>: It takes 1 minute to treat deadly wounds, and longterm care requires a medical bay or medical lab.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"pi80ytilFIJJC6to"}
{"name":"Mobility (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can easily move past dangerous foes.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Dex 13.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain a +4 bonus to your Armor Class against attacks of opportunity that you provoke by leaving a threatened square.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"K1DuZQv4CKQHxnIk"}
{"name":"Multi-Weapon Fighting (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You know how to fight with several lighter weapons at once and how to take advantage of your multiple attacks.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: When you make a full attack with two or more small arms or with two or more operative melee weapons (see page 184), reduce the penalty for making a full attack by 1.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"01aOr5z3Qc2xV8Ml"}
{"name":"Mystic Strike (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your magical power flows into your weapons.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Ability to cast spells.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: Your melee and ranged attacks count as magic for the purposes of bypassing damage reduction and other situations, such as attacking incorporeal creatures.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"v0ogh63XyYuth2uh"}
{"name":"Penetrating Attack (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You know how to angle your attacks so that you penetrate your opponent’s defenses.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Base attack bonus +12.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: Reduce your target’s energy resistances and damage reduction by 5 against your weapon attacks.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"IILK03DmelCL6eLJ"}
{"name":"Penetrating Spell","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You know how to cast spells so that they penetrate your opponent’s defenses.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Ability to cast 4th-level spells.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: Reduce your target’s energy resistances and damage reduction by 5 against your spell damage.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"uxBqhSrehoVgYvJF"}
{"name":"Powered Armored Proficiency (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You know how to use powered armor.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Str 13, base attack bonus +5, proficiency in light and heavy armor.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain proficiency in powered armor (see Armor Proficiency on page 242).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"XFUghykvnCSVHJ9n"}
{"name":"Psychic Power","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You have a natural psychic ability.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Cha 13, Minor Psychic Power, character level 4th.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: Select one of the following 1st-level spells: <em>comprehend languages</em>, <em>detect thoughts</em>, or <em>mind link</em>. You can cast this spell once per day as a spell-like ability, using your character level as your caster level.<br></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Special</strong>: You can select this feat more than once. Each time you do, you must choose a different spell from the list.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"5a0a2zXORbPi09Hu"}
{"name":"Pull the Pin (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can activate a foe’s grenade.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Improved Combat Maneuver (disarm).</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: When you make a successful disarm combat maneuver against a foe that you know has grenades, rather than disarming the foe of a weapon, you can activate one grenade in the foe’s possession. You can activate only a grenade that is ready to be drawn and thrown (not, for example, a grenade stowed away within an equipment pack). The grenade explodes at the end of your current turn, unless it has a delayed fuse that causes it to go off 1 round or more after it is activated.<br></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\">The foe takes a –2 penalty to the saving throw against this grenade, and the grenade’s explosion has half its normal area.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"KLehnmCfeY4Diqrv"}
{"name":"Quick Draw (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can draw weapons faster than most.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Base attack bonus +1.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You can draw a weapon as a swift action. Additionally, when making an attack using a thrown weapon as an attack or full attack action, you can draw a weapon as part of the action of making a thrown attack with it. You can draw a hidden weapon (see Sleight of Hand on page 146) as a move action.<br></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Normal</strong>: You can draw a weapon as a move action, or (if your base attack bonus is +1 or higher) as part of a move action, and you can draw a hidden weapon as a standard action.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"Yw2BRG4gk46kyCL6"}
{"name":"Reflect Projectiles (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can use your melee weapon to redirect attacks.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Deflect Projectiles, base attack bonus +16.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: When you successfully deflect an attack with the Deflect Projectiles feat, you can spend 1 additional Resolve Point to redirect the attack at a target within 60 feet to which you have line of effect. Make a ranged attack at a –4 penalty against the appropriate Armor Class of the new target. If your attack succeeds, the target is damaged as if it had been the target of the original attack.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"p4VfJtY8XSUIGdeV"}
{"name":"Shot on the Run (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can move, fire a ranged weapon, and move again before your foes can react.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Dex 15, Mobility, base attack bonus +4.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: As a full action, you can move up to your speed and make a single ranged attack at any point during your movement. If you have the trick attack class feature, you can take your movement from trick attack at any time during a trick attack (see page 93) with a ranged weapon (instead of only before).<br></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Normal</strong>: You can move only before or after an attack with a ranged weapon, not both.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"ACti4nBLewJMvG8R"}
{"name":"Skill Focus","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You are particularly adept at a certain skill.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Benefit</strong>: Choose a skill. You gain a +3 insight bonus to checks involving the chosen skill.</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Special</strong>: You can take this feat multiple times. Its effects don’t stack. Each time you take this feat, it applies to a new skill.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"dkDzFtHOTXLnJivf"}
{"name":"Skill Synergy","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You understand how two skills work well together.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: Choose two skills. These skills become class skills for you. If one or both were already class skills, you gain a +2 insight bonus to those skill checks instead.<br></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Special</strong>: You can take this feat multiple times. Its effects don’t stack. Each time you take it, it applies to two different skills.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"ZCs2NGwo5y2rUkRs"}
{"name":"Slippery Shooter (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You leave fewer openings when making a ranged attack.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Dex 15, base attack bonus +6.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain a +3 bonus to your Armor Class against attacks of opportunity you provoke by making a ranged attack.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"KKokTVjGbpDsLTe8"}
{"name":"Small Arm Proficiency (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You know how to use small arms.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain proficiency in small arms (see Weapon Proficiency on page 243).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"eXD7gTA4afwSdif2"}
{"name":"Sniper Weapon Proficiency (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You know how to use sniper weapons.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain proficiency in sniper weapons (see Weapon Proficiency on page 243).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"tg2n4TYVfxuELJsY"}
{"name":"Spell Focus","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Through careful study, you have developed methods to make your spells harder to resist.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Ability to cast spells, character level 3rd.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: The DC of spells you cast increases by 1. At 11th level, the DC of your spells instead increases by 2, and at 17th level, the DC of spells you cast instead increases by 3. This bonus does not apply to spell-like abilities.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"X0Vh8DqE3ZSpyXpC"}
{"name":"Spell Penetration","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your spells break through spell resistance more easily than those of other spellcasters.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain a +2 bonus to caster level checks to overcome a creature’s spell resistance (see page 265).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"S5lEh2oJ8VW1gVlP"}
{"name":"Spellbane","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your mind and body are fortified against magic.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Unable to cast spells or use spell-like abilities.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: You gain a +2 insight bonus to saving throws against spells and spell-like abilities. If you ever gain the ability to cast spells or use spell-like abilities, you lose the benefits of this feat and can replace it with Great Fortitude, Lightning Reflexes, or Iron Will, or the improved version of one of those feats if you meet its prerequisites.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"2f6iEn9ZI8vecE2k"}
{"name":"Suppressive Fire (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can use automatic weapons to create a cone of covering fire or harrying fire.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Base attack bonus +1, proficiency with heavy weapons.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: As a full action, you can use a ranged weapon with the automatic weapon property to provide covering fire or harrying fire in a cone with a range equal to half the weapon’s range increment. You must expend 10 charges or rounds of ammunition to use this ability. Decide if you are providing covering fire or harrying fire. Make a single ranged attack roll with a +4 bonus, and compare it to the AC of all creatures in the area. Any creature with an AC equal to or less than your attack roll is affected by the selected effect. If you select covering fire, choose a single ally that gains the benefit of the covering fire bonus to its AC.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"Bl1Dw3CX7Brl1AC2"}
{"name":"Technomantic Dabbler","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You dabble with coding in the language of magic.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Intelligence 15, character level 5th, no levels in technomancer.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: Choose two 0-level technomancer spells and one 1st-level technomancer spell. You can cast the 0-level spells at will and the 1st-level spell once per day for every 3 character levels you have. Your caster level is equal to your character level, and the key ability score for these spells is Intelligence. If you later gain levels in technomancer, you lose the benefits of this feat and can replace it with either Spell Focus or Spell Penetration.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"xBENKYPlDKF0yGp1"}
{"name":"Toughness","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You have enhanced physical resilience, and harsh conditions or long exertions don’t easily tire you.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: For every character level you have (and whenever you gain a new level), you gain 1 Stamina Point. In addition, you gain a +4 bonus to Constitution checks to continue running, to avoid damage from a forced march, to hold your breath, and to avoid damage from starvation or thirst. You also gain a +4 bonus to Fortitude saving throws to avoid taking damage from hot or cold environments, to withstand the harmful effects of thick and thin atmospheres, to avoid choking when breathing in heavy smoke, and to avoid fatigue caused by sleep deprivation.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"F9H8iEN8FUXIOUM2"}
{"name":"Unfriendly Fire (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can trick foes into firing at an unintended target.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Bluff 5 ranks.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: As a reaction when an attacker makes a ranged attack against you and misses, you can attempt a Bluff check to redirect the attack toward a different target. The new target must be adjacent to you and within line of sight and line of effect of the original attacker. The DC for this check is equal to either 10 + the attacker’s total Sense Motive skill bonus, or 15 + 1-1/2 × the attacker’s CR, whichever is greater. You can’t take 10 on this check. If you succeed, the original attacker rerolls the attack roll (see page 243) with the same bonuses against the appropriate Armor Class of the new target.<br></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\">Once a creature has observed you use this feat, even if that creature is neither the attacker nor the new target, you can’t use this feat to attempt to redirect attacks from that creature for 24 hours.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"8XbdswneZ2WPtXS6"}
{"name":"Veiled Threat","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can be so subtle not even the people you threaten are entirely sure you threatened them.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Cha 15, Intimidate 1 rank.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: When you successfully use the Intimidate skill to bully a creature, after the duration of its helpful attitude ends, its attitude toward you becomes indifferent rather than hostile.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"eveZktyLn2XmmBoK"}
{"name":"Weapon Specialization (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You know how to get the full damage out of a weapon type your class doesn’t normally use.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Character level 3rd, proficiency with selected weapon type.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: Choose one weapon type (small arms, longarms, heavy weapons, etc.). You gain specialization in that weapon type, which means you add your character level to damage with the selected weapon type, or half your character level for small arms or operative melee weapons. You can never have specialization in grenades.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"9Us7Eg9cAoq3BcS5"}
{"name":"Weapon Focus (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"QKfICymYNdnzinV1":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You have increased training in a particular weapon type, making it easier to hit your target.<br><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Proficiency with selected weapon type.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Benefit</strong>: Chose one weapon type (small arms, longarms, heavy weapons, etc.). You gain a +1 bonus to attack rolls with that weapon type. If your base attack bonus is at least 3 lower than your character level (or your mechanic’s class level, if you are a drone), you gain a +2 bonus instead.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Core Rulebook","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":"negate"},"descriptors":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"bMZTC3m95OSPFlTG"}
